SIMPLE: episcopalian
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Episcopalian
<hw>E*pis`co*pa"li*an</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Pertaining
to bishops, or government by bishops; episcopal; specifically, of or
relating to the Protestant Episcopal Church.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Episcopalian</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Episcopalian
<hw>E*pis`co*pa"li*an</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>One who belongs to an
episcopal church, or adheres to the episcopal form of church government
and discipline; a churchman; specifically, in the United States, a
member of the Protestant Episcopal Church.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Episcopalianism</ent>⟦br⟧
